# Vercel AI SDK — Flashcard Generation

This app uses the [`ai`](https://sdk.vercel.ai) npm package to call OpenAI for **AI flashcard generation** (Pro feature). All AI calls run **server-side only** — never from Client Components or Route Handlers triggered by the UI.

## Environment

Set `OPENAI_API_KEY` in `.env.local`. Never expose it via `NEXT_PUBLIC_*`.

## Structured output — array of flashcards

Use `generateText` with `Output.object` and a Zod schema. The model must return an object with a `cards` array; each item has `front` and `back` (matching [db/schema.ts](mdc:db/schema.ts)).

```typescript
import { generateText, Output } from "ai";
import { z } from "zod";

const GeneratedFlashcardsSchema = z.object({
  cards: z.array(
    z.object({
      front: z.string().min(1),
      back: z.string().min(1),
    }),
  ),
});

export async function generateFlashcards(topic: string, count: number) {
  const { output } = await generateText({
    model: "openai/gpt-5.3-chat",
    output: Output.object({
      schema: GeneratedFlashcardsSchema,
    }),
    prompt: `Generate exactly ${count} flashcards about: ${topic}. Put a concise question or term on the front and the answer on the back. Return only the structured object.`,
  });

  if (output.cards.length !== count) {
    throw new Error("AI returned an unexpected number of cards");
  }

  return output.cards;
}
```

Put pure generation logic in `lib/ai/` (no auth, no DB). Keep the Zod **input** schema and orchestration in a Server Action under [app/actions/](mdc:app/actions/).

## Server Action pattern

Follow [data-access.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/data-access.mdc) and [clerk-billing.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/clerk-billing.mdc):

1. Validate typed input with Zod (`deckId`, `topic`, `count`).
2. `auth()` — require `userId` and `has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })`.
3. Call `generateFlashcards()` from `lib/ai/`.
4. Persist each card via [db/queries/cards.ts](mdc:db/queries/cards.ts) — never inline Drizzle in the action.
5. `revalidatePath` for the deck page.

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD — action validates, gates Pro, delegates AI + DB
const { userId, has } = await auth();
if (!userId) throw new Error("Unauthorized");
if (!has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })) {
  throw new Error("AI generation requires a Pro subscription.");
}

const generated = await generateFlashcards(parsed.data.topic, parsed.data.count);
for (const card of generated) {
  await createCardRecord(parsed.data.deckId, userId, card);
}
```

```typescript
// ❌ BAD — AI call in a Client Component or ungated action
"use client";
const cards = await generateFlashcards(topic, 10);

// ❌ BAD — trusting client-supplied userId or skipping feature check
```

## UI

Hide the generate control with Clerk `<Show when={{ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" }}>` and a pricing fallback. Trigger must be a shadcn `<Button>` per [shadcn-ui.mdc](mdc:.cursor/rules/shadcn-ui.mdc).

## Rules summary

| Concern | Where |
|---------|--------|
| OpenAI call + output schema | `lib/ai/` |
| Input Zod, auth, billing, revalidate | Server Action in `app/actions/` |
| Insert cards | `db/queries/cards.ts` |
| Pro entitlement | `has({ feature: "ai_flashcard_generation" })` server-side |
